80
00:07:53,246 --> 00:07:54,455
-What do we do?
-What do we do?

81
00:07:54,664 --> 00:07:56,291
Gosh, Jeong Hyeok!

82
00:08:12,807 --> 00:08:14,434
<i>I must pull myself together and focus.</i>

83
00:08:15,226 --> 00:08:17,312
<i>Think, whatever it is.</i>

84
00:08:18,396 --> 00:08:20,732
<i>Yes, I should think happy thoughts.</i>

85
00:08:21,441 --> 00:08:22,650
<i>Something that makes me happy.</i>

86
00:08:28,740 --> 00:08:31,367
<i>Jeong Hyeok boiling noodles.</i>

87
00:08:33,995 --> 00:08:38,207
<i>Jeong Hyeok who didn't know the difference
between candles and scented candles.</i>

88
00:08:41,294 --> 00:08:44,631
<i>But now he knows the difference.</i>

89
00:09:04,901 --> 00:09:06,778
<i>Jeong Hyeok who covers me with a blanket</i>

90
00:09:06,945 --> 00:09:08,947
<i>on his way
to get himself a glass of water.</i>

91
00:09:10,531 --> 00:09:12,158
I'll see you off.

92
00:09:12,784 --> 00:09:14,661
-No need.
-All is well.

93
00:09:14,744 --> 00:09:17,121
I'll be fine after taking medication
and going to bed.

94
00:09:18,122 --> 00:09:19,082
I'm fine.

95
00:09:19,165 --> 00:09:21,125
<i>Jeong Hyeok who always lies</i>

96
00:09:21,209 --> 00:09:24,087
<i>and says that he's fine
even though everything is going astray.</i>

97
00:09:25,296 --> 00:09:27,840
Then you'll be safe.
As long as you stay in my sight.

98
00:09:27,924 --> 00:09:30,468
Tell me what you see. I can find you.

99
00:09:31,177 --> 00:09:33,888
<i>Does he think he's a superhero or what?</i>

100
00:09:34,514 --> 00:09:37,976
<i>He always says that he can do anything
and find me no matter where I am.</i>

101
00:09:38,559 --> 00:09:41,729
<i>Jeong Hyeok likes to talk bullshit
and bluff.</i>

102
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:47,151
I miss you.

103
00:10:49,017 --> 00:10:53,414
CRASH LANDING ON YOU

104
00:11:09,942 --> 00:11:11,277
Where am I?

105
00:11:20,244 --> 00:11:22,080
Hello? Is anybody there?

106
00:11:23,915 --> 00:11:25,958
Is anyone outside? Hello?

107
00:11:35,176 --> 00:11:36,219
Right.

108
00:11:37,637 --> 00:11:39,555
They wouldn't have locked me up here

109
00:11:40,556 --> 00:11:41,891
if they were going to let me out.

110
00:11:49,315 --> 00:11:50,608
Some bastards

111
00:11:51,692 --> 00:11:53,569
abducted me and locked me up here.

112
00:11:54,195 --> 00:11:55,446
Why didn't they kill me?

113
00:11:57,365 --> 00:11:58,491
What are they after?

114
00:12:04,831 --> 00:12:07,416
Are they watching me right now?

115
00:12:17,844 --> 00:12:19,095
Who are you?

116
00:12:25,205 --> 00:12:28,604
RUN AWAY AND YOU DIE!
LET'S BUILD A STRONG SOCIALIST COUNTRY

117
00:12:34,527 --> 00:12:36,028
As you probably know,

118
00:12:36,112 --> 00:12:39,657
it's not easy for regular soldiers like us
to come here.

119
00:12:40,575 --> 00:12:44,162
But my childhood friend
just so happens to be

120
00:12:44,245 --> 00:12:48,624
working as a high-ranking officer
at this detention center.

121
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:52,044
I don't think he deserves
to take credit for it though.

122
00:12:52,128 --> 00:12:53,171
I agree.

123
00:12:53,254 --> 00:12:54,839
I mean, whose fault is it to begin with?

124
00:12:54,922 --> 00:12:57,216
Dan's mother came by the other day.

125
00:12:57,300 --> 00:13:02,471
Master Sergeant Pyo got drunk that day
and told her everything about Se-ri.

126
00:13:04,348 --> 00:13:08,686
I mean, not everything about her.

127
00:13:08,769 --> 00:13:12,148
I heard her mother is a rich businesswoman
who owns a department store in Pyongyang.

128
00:13:12,648 --> 00:13:16,194
Maybe she hired some people to track
Se-ri down and did something to her.

129
00:13:16,652 --> 00:13:19,363
Hey, no way.

130
00:13:19,447 --> 00:13:21,908
I've seen it so many times
in those South Korean dramas.

131
00:13:23,075 --> 00:13:25,119
When someone interferes
with their kid's wedding,

132
00:13:25,454 --> 00:13:29,248
the rich in the South either splash water
on that person's face or give money.

133
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:34,128
But the rich here are tougher,

134
00:13:34,712 --> 00:13:37,632
so maybe she abducted her
to teach her a lesson.

135
00:13:38,090 --> 00:13:43,026
Captain Ri, that lady didn't seem like
she could do such a thing.

136
00:13:45,115 --> 00:13:46,015
I'm warning you.

137
00:13:47,225 --> 00:13:49,310
Don't do anything you're going to regret.

138
00:13:50,144 --> 00:13:51,395
Comrades.

139
00:13:51,938 --> 00:13:54,023
I need you to do something for me.

140
00:13:56,025 --> 00:13:57,151
Only after getting locked up,

141
00:13:58,611 --> 00:14:00,279
you called me and said
you wanted to see me

142
00:14:01,447 --> 00:14:02,698
for the first time ever.

143
00:14:06,911 --> 00:14:08,079
That woman is gone.

144
00:14:10,373 --> 00:14:11,249
So?

145
00:14:11,832 --> 00:14:13,876
You must know something about it.

146
00:14:16,128 --> 00:14:17,171
Who did it?

147
00:14:17,588 --> 00:14:19,048
Where was she taken to?

148
00:14:20,091 --> 00:14:21,217
And is she

149
00:14:22,301 --> 00:14:23,970
-okay?
-How ridiculous.

150
00:14:25,304 --> 00:14:27,014
Your wedding is in a few days,

151
00:14:27,890 --> 00:14:30,017
but you're worried about another woman.

152
00:14:30,518 --> 00:14:32,478
You look as if you've lost everything.

153
00:14:34,605 --> 00:14:36,315
This is actually good.

154
00:14:37,733 --> 00:14:42,145
You should stay locked up here
until the day of our wedding

155
00:14:43,739 --> 00:14:45,032
and just come out on that day.

156
00:14:46,450 --> 00:14:47,326
I'll see you then.

157
00:14:48,202 --> 00:14:49,370
Is it my father?

158
00:14:58,963 --> 00:15:00,798
You told me
not to do anything I'll regret.

159
00:15:02,550 --> 00:15:04,719
Whom did you ask for help
to make me regret my actions?

160
00:15:06,470 --> 00:15:08,180
It can't be the State Security Department.

161
00:15:09,307 --> 00:15:11,142
And there's no way your mother did it.

162
00:15:12,643 --> 00:15:13,853
Did you

163
00:15:14,437 --> 00:15:15,938
meet my father?

164
00:15:18,107 --> 00:15:19,525
Did my father

165
00:15:21,444 --> 00:15:24,280
-take her? That woman--
-That's right. She's dead.

166
00:15:25,281 --> 00:15:26,866
You won't ever find her.

167
00:15:27,575 --> 00:15:29,327
So you should just give up.

168
00:15:31,495 --> 00:15:32,747
Go and tell my father.

169
00:15:34,373 --> 00:15:36,792
If he hurts or harms her in any way,

170
00:15:37,626 --> 00:15:39,712
he'll lose even the only son he has left
for good.

171
00:15:42,298 --> 00:15:43,466
You'd better tell him.

172
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:03,110
IDEOLOGICAL DISCIPLINE

173
00:16:11,952 --> 00:16:13,996
Should I have gone in with you?

174
00:16:14,705 --> 00:16:15,873
How's Jeong Hyeok holding up?

175
00:16:16,957 --> 00:16:19,794
Director Ri doesn't know
about this yet, right?

176
00:16:20,669 --> 00:16:23,255
How did he end up in the detention center?

177
00:16:23,339 --> 00:16:25,758
-He'll be furious when he finds out.
-Just leave him.

178
00:16:27,134 --> 00:16:28,010
What?

179
00:16:28,636 --> 00:16:30,888
Hey, your wedding
is just around the corner.

180
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:33,307
I have to keep him there

181
00:16:35,643 --> 00:16:37,019
to marry him.

182
00:16:37,603 --> 00:16:39,980
I'm not following at all.
Can you elaborate?

183
00:16:48,948 --> 00:16:49,990
U Pil.

184
00:16:51,075 --> 00:16:52,618
-Dad.
-Gosh.

185
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:56,321
What brings you here?

186
00:16:57,957 --> 00:17:02,525
Yesterday, some men came
and took that pretty lady from the South.

187
00:17:03,379 --> 00:17:06,632
And she dropped this.

188
00:18:04,023 --> 00:18:04,940
U Pil.

189
00:18:05,733 --> 00:18:07,234
Have you shown this to anyone else?

190
00:18:09,069 --> 00:18:11,363
Don't tell anyone about this, okay?

191
00:18:11,447 --> 00:18:12,531
Okay, Dad.

192
00:18:13,157 --> 00:18:15,201
Will she be okay though?

193
00:18:24,293 --> 00:18:27,588
They say you never know
what someone is really thinking.

194
00:18:27,671 --> 00:18:30,758
We've known him for a long time.
I can't believe he fooled us all along.

195
00:18:31,342 --> 00:18:33,177
I don't understand Captain Ri.

196
00:18:33,802 --> 00:18:37,556
He's not the type
to brag about his family background.

197
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:39,767
-Exactly.
-Still.

198
00:18:40,351 --> 00:18:43,229
This is huge news.
How could he keep it from us?

199
00:18:43,896 --> 00:18:47,149
Captain Ri's father is the Director
of the General Political Bureau?

200
00:18:48,776 --> 00:18:50,569
I still can't believe it.

201
00:18:50,736 --> 00:18:53,072
Director Ri
won't sit still if he finds out

202
00:18:53,697 --> 00:18:56,367
that his dear son is locked up
in the detention center.

203
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:58,077
Shouldn't we tell him?

204
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:02,456
Captain Ri told us not to tell anyone,

205
00:19:02,957 --> 00:19:03,999
so keep your lips sealed.

206
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:05,417
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

207
00:19:05,501 --> 00:19:06,335
Let's go.

208
00:19:23,936 --> 00:19:25,813
Everyone probably heard it, right?

209
00:19:27,314 --> 00:19:28,941
I think you were a little too quiet.

210
00:19:29,024 --> 00:19:31,569
It'd look suspicious
if we were chatting about it loudly.

211
00:19:32,069 --> 00:19:34,947
But will that be enough
for the word to spread?

212
00:19:35,364 --> 00:19:36,615
Hey.

213
00:19:36,949 --> 00:19:40,828
You don't need 100 bees
to get 100 flowers to bloom.

214
00:19:41,579 --> 00:19:45,833
It will only take half a day
for it to reach everyone in this area.

215
00:19:47,334 --> 00:19:48,669
But the problem is,

216
00:19:50,170 --> 00:19:53,090
whether or not it's true.

217
00:19:53,173 --> 00:19:55,134
There's something else I need you to do.

218
00:19:56,218 --> 00:19:58,596
Spread rumors about my family background,

219
00:19:59,722 --> 00:20:01,390
that my father is the Director

220
00:20:03,058 --> 00:20:04,351
of the General Political Bureau.

221
00:20:09,732 --> 00:20:13,444
I don't think he'll get me out of here
even if he finds out that I'm here.

222
00:20:14,069 --> 00:20:17,698
I want to spread rumors to find a way
to get out, so I need your help.

223
00:20:21,118 --> 00:20:22,161
I told you.

224
00:20:22,703 --> 00:20:24,538
He must've hurt his head when he got shot.

225
00:20:24,622 --> 00:20:26,081
Don't worry, Master Sergeant Pyo.

226
00:20:27,166 --> 00:20:28,167
All of it is true.

227
00:20:29,752 --> 00:20:31,128
I don't have time.

228
00:20:31,211 --> 00:20:34,840
The rumors must reach the Senior Colonel
as quickly as possible.

229
00:20:35,799 --> 00:20:39,219
His father is the Director
of the General Political Bureau?

230
00:20:40,012 --> 00:20:43,766
What if it's complete bullshit
and we got fooled?

231
00:20:43,849 --> 00:20:46,769
Shouldn't you know him better by now?
He'd never do that.

232
00:20:51,857 --> 00:20:55,861
His father is the Director
of the General Political Bureau?

233
00:20:55,944 --> 00:20:58,155
That's right. My husband

234
00:20:58,238 --> 00:21:01,450
heard his colleagues talk about it.

235
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,286
I have to say, there was

236
00:21:05,329 --> 00:21:06,664
something different about him.

237
00:21:07,331 --> 00:21:10,709
I mean, his looks alone are revolutionary.

238
00:21:10,793 --> 00:21:13,128
And the way he talks and walks.

239
00:21:13,212 --> 00:21:16,382
I always thought he looked
too confident for a captain.

240
00:21:16,465 --> 00:21:18,258
-Exactly.
-Yes, totally.

241
00:21:18,342 --> 00:21:21,387
To be honest,
when I saw his broad shoulders,

242
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:23,847
I knew that he was special.

243
00:21:24,639 --> 00:21:26,183
-His shoulders?
-Yes.

244
00:21:26,850 --> 00:21:27,685
Think about it.

245
00:21:28,268 --> 00:21:32,398
He can show off those broad shoulders
because someone's got his back.

246
00:21:32,773 --> 00:21:37,027
If he'd ever been intimidated by anyone
since he was little,

247
00:21:37,111 --> 00:21:40,906
he wouldn't have
such incredibly broad shoulders.

248
00:21:41,490 --> 00:21:44,743
-She has a point.
-That's a good theory.

249
00:21:44,827 --> 00:21:46,453
-Right?
-Good point.

250
00:21:46,870 --> 00:21:48,455
DEMILITARIZED ZONE

