253
00:21:52,626 --> 00:21:55,295
-An emergency!
-<i>A deserter from Stakeout Squad 31.</i>

254
00:21:55,796 --> 00:21:57,881
<i>A deserter from Stakeout Squad 31.</i>

255
00:21:58,048 --> 00:22:00,175
<i>What? Another deserter?</i>

256
00:22:02,803 --> 00:22:05,681
Tell everyone to be on standby.
Where is Lieutenant Commander Cho?

257
00:22:07,224 --> 00:22:08,058
Pyongyang?

258
00:22:08,142 --> 00:22:10,060
Why at this critical time?

259
00:22:10,144 --> 00:22:11,311
"Spy education"?

260
00:22:12,062 --> 00:22:13,355
Goodness. Fine.

261
00:22:15,649 --> 00:22:18,736
-Could you prepare my dinner now?
-I heard about it.

262
00:22:18,819 --> 00:22:19,820
About what?

263
00:22:21,739 --> 00:22:22,698
Captain Ri Jeong Hyeok.

264
00:22:23,949 --> 00:22:25,617
I heard he went to the detention center.

265
00:22:26,452 --> 00:22:29,538
Young people these days have no respect.

266
00:22:29,621 --> 00:22:31,915
I mean, he defied his superior.
What was he thinking?

267
00:22:31,999 --> 00:22:34,501
That punk won't be seeing
any sunlight for a while.

268
00:22:34,710 --> 00:22:36,837
Have you ever wondered

269
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:41,467
why Captain Ri was being disrespectful?

270
00:22:42,885 --> 00:22:44,803
It's because he's got no morals,
of course.

271
00:22:45,429 --> 00:22:47,431
He was the one who tipped off
the Trial Bureau,

272
00:22:47,514 --> 00:22:49,892
which is why Cho Cheol Gang
and I were investigated.

273
00:22:49,975 --> 00:22:52,186
He kept digging around
and it was one hell of a headache.

274
00:22:52,269 --> 00:22:55,189
Why do you think he's got so much nerve

275
00:22:55,709 --> 00:22:58,776
to poke around, dig around,
and nose around?

276
00:22:59,359 --> 00:23:01,361
You keep beating around the bush.

277
00:23:01,445 --> 00:23:03,656
Just tell me what your point is.

278
00:23:04,948 --> 00:23:06,408
Have you

279
00:23:06,992 --> 00:23:10,287
ever met the Director
of the General Political Bureau?

280
00:23:10,370 --> 00:23:13,540
How can I meet such a high officer?

281
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:16,835
Why? Does anyone have the connection?

282
00:23:16,919 --> 00:23:18,420
There was, indeed.

283
00:23:18,921 --> 00:23:21,089
But someone just cut it off.

284
00:23:21,173 --> 00:23:23,217
Who did that?
What kind of a psycho would do that?

285
00:23:24,343 --> 00:23:26,887
-It was you!
-Gosh! What's wrong?

286
00:23:26,970 --> 00:23:28,972
Ri Jeong Hyeok was born
with the connection

287
00:23:29,056 --> 00:23:30,974
to the Director
of the General Political Bureau.

288
00:23:31,058 --> 00:23:33,143
What? How does he have the connection?

289
00:23:33,852 --> 00:23:37,064
Ri Jeong Hyeok is the son of the Director
of the General Political Bureau!

290
00:23:37,856 --> 00:23:38,982
What?

291
00:23:40,692 --> 00:23:43,487
I told you to give him
the Preferential Star.

292
00:23:44,071 --> 00:23:45,656
But you just gave it to a random man.

293
00:23:45,739 --> 00:23:46,865
What? He can't see sunlight?

294
00:23:46,949 --> 00:23:49,535
Your life is never
going to see sunlight now.

295
00:23:49,618 --> 00:23:51,662
What are you going to do now? Tell me!

296
00:23:51,745 --> 00:23:52,913
Where are you going?

297
00:24:09,096 --> 00:24:10,222
Who are you?

298
00:24:11,390 --> 00:24:12,516
What are you doing?

299
00:24:27,030 --> 00:24:28,031
Have some tea.

300
00:24:38,876 --> 00:24:40,294
It's pine mushroom tea.

301
00:24:41,044 --> 00:24:42,880
It smells good, and I appreciate it

302
00:24:44,756 --> 00:24:45,841
but I won't drink it.

303
00:24:46,341 --> 00:24:48,886
It's not like
I was invited here as a guest.

304
00:24:48,969 --> 00:24:51,513
I won't just drink
whatever you tell me to drink.

305
00:24:51,597 --> 00:24:52,848
I'm not that dumb.

306
00:24:53,348 --> 00:24:54,725
Where do you think you are?

307
00:24:57,644 --> 00:24:59,980
You're her father, right?

308
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,025
You don't have to be surprised.

309
00:25:04,526 --> 00:25:07,154
You look just like Ms. Seo Dan.

310
00:25:08,989 --> 00:25:11,450
Your mouth, nose,

311
00:25:11,825 --> 00:25:12,868
and especially

312
00:25:13,118 --> 00:25:15,621
your glaring eyes

313
00:25:15,704 --> 00:25:17,789
look just like hers.

314
00:25:18,498 --> 00:25:19,875
-Is that so?
-Yes.

315
00:25:19,958 --> 00:25:24,254
I'm quicker and more sensitive
than others at this kind of thing.

316
00:25:25,756 --> 00:25:26,715
I see.

317
00:25:27,549 --> 00:25:30,010
To be honest,
when I was first dragged here,

318
00:25:30,093 --> 00:25:34,056
I was so upset
and wondered who would do this,

319
00:25:36,058 --> 00:25:38,393
but now I get it.

320
00:25:39,353 --> 00:25:40,479
You get it?

321
00:25:40,562 --> 00:25:44,816
You think I'm in the way of your daughter.

322
00:25:45,859 --> 00:25:48,487
You think I'm coming between the two,

323
00:25:49,738 --> 00:25:52,032
and I totally understand.

324
00:25:55,118 --> 00:25:56,912
Okay. Then tell me.

325
00:25:57,496 --> 00:26:00,457
What was your purpose
of approaching Ri Jeong Hyeok

326
00:26:00,540 --> 00:26:01,875
and staying with him?

327
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:06,463
"Purpose"? That's absolutely unfair.

328
00:26:06,546 --> 00:26:08,256
I am

329
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,801
a pure victim
of a second of the military gap

330
00:26:10,884 --> 00:26:13,720
created by a momentary error
of the defense system

331
00:26:13,971 --> 00:26:16,390
of the South and North Korea

332
00:26:16,473 --> 00:26:19,267
caused by a strong and unexpected storm.

333
00:26:20,811 --> 00:26:22,813
-What?
-It was an accident.

334
00:26:24,856 --> 00:26:26,733
Sir, please think about it.

335
00:26:27,317 --> 00:26:29,945
I'm running a company in South Korea.

336
00:26:30,028 --> 00:26:33,073
It's not just a tiny store
but an enormous fashion company.

337
00:26:34,032 --> 00:26:37,703
This might sound like bragging,
but we have 14 branches abroad.

338
00:26:39,037 --> 00:26:41,248
So for what purpose would I come here

339
00:26:41,331 --> 00:26:44,042
to put myself in trouble?

340
00:26:44,126 --> 00:26:45,252
I am just

341
00:26:46,378 --> 00:26:49,506
an innocent citizen of Seoul
who has been worrying

342
00:26:49,589 --> 00:26:52,384
about what I should do with all that money

343
00:26:52,843 --> 00:26:57,180
and if I will ever get to use
all the money before I die.

344
00:26:57,681 --> 00:27:02,894
And Ri Jeong Hyeok helped me
out of humanity.

345
00:27:03,562 --> 00:27:07,107
So are you saying
Ri Jeong Hyeok caused all this?

346
00:27:07,858 --> 00:27:09,359
What? No.

347
00:27:09,651 --> 00:27:11,403
That's not what I meant.

348
00:27:11,653 --> 00:27:13,947
He hasn't done anything wrong.

349
00:27:14,406 --> 00:27:16,408
I'm telling you.
He didn't do anything wrong.

350
00:27:16,908 --> 00:27:19,327
I want to make that clear at least.

351
00:27:19,411 --> 00:27:20,579
He didn't do anything wrong?

352
00:27:20,912 --> 00:27:23,331
He hid an unidentified person
from South Korea.

353
00:27:23,415 --> 00:27:26,501
At first, he tried to report me.

354
00:27:26,585 --> 00:27:28,837
But I threatened him.

355
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,590
"If you report me, I will tell them

356
00:27:31,673 --> 00:27:34,051
you and your men did
a poor job at guarding."

357
00:27:34,801 --> 00:27:36,678
So he had to make

358
00:27:37,179 --> 00:27:39,806
an inevitable decision
for his subordinates.

359
00:27:41,058 --> 00:27:43,894
So is that all about your relationship?

360
00:27:47,564 --> 00:27:49,608
To be honest,

361
00:27:50,108 --> 00:27:51,526
I liked Ri Jeong Hyeok

362
00:27:52,486 --> 00:27:53,862
a lot.

363
00:27:55,781 --> 00:27:58,700
It just happened. I'm so sorry.

364
00:27:58,825 --> 00:28:02,287
He didn't like me back though.
It was one-sided. You don't need to worry.

365
00:28:02,788 --> 00:28:05,415
He must be thinking
I'm back in my country now.

366
00:28:05,499 --> 00:28:06,750
I'm sure he doesn't care at all.

367
00:28:08,418 --> 00:28:09,628
So, sir,

368
00:28:11,004 --> 00:28:12,339
please help me.

369
00:28:12,422 --> 00:28:13,256
Me?

370
00:28:14,257 --> 00:28:16,426
You hired some men to kidnap me.

371
00:28:16,927 --> 00:28:21,181
Obviously, you have some power.
That's why I'm asking.

372
00:28:22,307 --> 00:28:24,101
Please be generous

373
00:28:24,184 --> 00:28:26,478
and help me go home in one piece.

374
00:28:27,437 --> 00:28:30,732
Actually, you know,
Ri Jeong Hyeok is just a captain.

375
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:34,152
He doesn't have any power.

376
00:28:34,611 --> 00:28:37,072
He doesn't have any power.

377
00:28:40,534 --> 00:28:43,870
If you help me this time,

378
00:28:44,621 --> 00:28:48,166
I promise to return your favor.

379
00:28:53,171 --> 00:28:54,172
Sir!

380
00:28:54,589 --> 00:28:56,216
Sir!

381
00:28:56,842 --> 00:28:57,884
Sir!

382
00:28:57,968 --> 00:28:59,136
Sir!

383
00:29:20,198 --> 00:29:21,241
Are you kidding me?

384
00:29:22,242 --> 00:29:24,327
I've been training myself
with intermittent fasting.

385
00:29:42,804 --> 00:29:46,057
I won't swallow
a single grain of rice here.

386
00:29:46,641 --> 00:29:47,809
I'm sorry.

387
00:29:48,393 --> 00:29:49,895
You haven't eaten anything today.

388
00:29:51,855 --> 00:29:54,441
If you think the food is poisoned,
I can try it for you.

389
00:29:57,194 --> 00:29:58,278
Who are you?

390
00:29:59,654 --> 00:30:00,697
Actually,

391
00:30:01,281 --> 00:30:02,616
that doesn't matter.

392
00:30:02,699 --> 00:30:04,618
Why did you bring me here?

393
00:30:05,202 --> 00:30:06,411
I'm sorry,

394
00:30:08,038 --> 00:30:09,748
but we can't help it either.

395
00:30:11,458 --> 00:30:13,418
The food is safe. You can eat it.

396
00:30:14,169 --> 00:30:15,253
Wait.

397
00:30:16,671 --> 00:30:17,881
Could you tell me

398
00:30:19,132 --> 00:30:20,133
if Ri Jeong Hyeok is...

399
00:30:25,847 --> 00:30:28,433
doing all right?

400
00:30:31,019 --> 00:30:34,189
I don't want him to be in trouble

401
00:30:34,272 --> 00:30:35,857
or be punished because of me.

402
00:30:36,024 --> 00:30:38,360
That's the last thing I want.

403
00:30:40,362 --> 00:30:42,405
Do you like him so much?

404
00:30:45,992 --> 00:30:47,077
Well...

405
00:30:48,620 --> 00:30:50,872
That's not it.

406
00:31:00,507 --> 00:31:02,801
It's unhealthy for a woman
to stay in a cold room like this.

407
00:31:22,654 --> 00:31:24,406
You should sleep here tonight.

408
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:25,949
By the way,

409
00:31:26,449 --> 00:31:29,411
who is the owner of this room?

410
00:31:30,245 --> 00:31:32,372
I believe one's bookshelves

411
00:31:32,455 --> 00:31:34,874
tell the person's personality,

412
00:31:34,958 --> 00:31:37,669
character, and taste.

413
00:31:39,004 --> 00:31:40,922
And these books

414
00:31:41,548 --> 00:31:43,967
remind me of someone I know.

415
00:31:45,802 --> 00:31:49,014
Dan, what was the room number?

416
00:31:57,105 --> 00:31:58,606
You're not

417
00:31:59,566 --> 00:32:00,650
Seo Dan's mother, are you?

418
00:32:04,112 --> 00:32:07,115
Are you Jeong Hyeok's mother?

419
00:32:10,493 --> 00:32:12,662
THE DAUGHTER OF QUEENS
AND THE CEO OF SE-RI'S CHOICE DIES

420
00:32:12,746 --> 00:32:14,164
<i>MYEONGSEONG DAILY NEWS</i>

421
00:32:16,249 --> 00:32:18,668
She's a daughter of a rich family
and was registered dead.

422
00:32:19,794 --> 00:32:22,464
Why on earth did she come here
and meet my son?

423
00:32:22,547 --> 00:32:24,424
You must not send her back.

424
00:32:25,008 --> 00:32:28,094
If she goes back to South Korea,
it will create a big buzz.

425
00:32:28,595 --> 00:32:32,265
It will cause something
you need to take responsibility for.

426
00:32:33,016 --> 00:32:35,143
The Military Director seems
to be up to something too.

427
00:32:35,727 --> 00:32:36,770
We don't have enough time.

428
00:32:36,853 --> 00:32:38,646
Just give me an order

429
00:32:38,730 --> 00:32:42,359
and I will take her out tonight
and take care of her quietly.

430
00:32:45,695 --> 00:32:47,530
Not at such a late hour.

431
00:32:48,114 --> 00:32:48,948
Excuse me, sir?

432
00:32:49,741 --> 00:32:53,286
My wife keeps insisting that we should
let her get some sleep at least.

433
00:32:53,370 --> 00:32:54,496
Oh, well.

434
00:32:56,414 --> 00:32:59,709
Let's wait and see for now.

435
00:33:31,074 --> 00:33:33,910
Goodness, Jeong Hyeok.

436
00:33:35,578 --> 00:33:37,163
Were you a child actor?

437
00:33:38,998 --> 00:33:42,001
You look so handsome among other kids.
That's just unfair.

438
00:33:49,092 --> 00:33:51,553
Look at the handwriting.

439
00:33:52,804 --> 00:33:54,514
So cute.

440
00:33:59,477 --> 00:34:05,483
I WANT TO BE A WORLD-FAMOUS PIANIST

441
00:34:05,567 --> 00:34:07,277
Did you want

442
00:34:08,278 --> 00:34:10,864
to become a pianist?

443
00:34:22,834 --> 00:34:23,918
But...

444
00:34:25,670 --> 00:34:26,963
you ended up being a soldier.

445
00:36:00,964 --> 00:36:02,178
Sir,

446
00:36:02,934 --> 00:36:06,479
I can let you visit him,
but bailing is a whole different matter.

447
00:36:06,563 --> 00:36:08,356
You're the head of the detention center.

448
00:36:08,439 --> 00:36:10,650
Bailing shouldn't be a big deal for you.

449
00:36:10,817 --> 00:36:12,610
He assaulted his superior,

450
00:36:12,694 --> 00:36:14,362
who was Battalion Security Officer.

451
00:36:15,196 --> 00:36:16,823
It was the worst kind of mutiny.

452
00:36:17,532 --> 00:36:20,952
The State Security Department
is pretty upset about it.

453
00:36:21,035 --> 00:36:25,707
You can't make it to the main position
if you're slow like that.

454
00:36:30,253 --> 00:36:32,005
Captain Ri's father is...

455
00:36:35,842 --> 00:36:39,596
My legs are still shaky.
I have no idea how I made it here.

456
00:36:40,930 --> 00:36:43,725
As a matter of fact,
as the head of the detention center,

457
00:36:43,808 --> 00:36:47,937
I did have fundamental doubts
about whether it was an assault case.

458
00:36:50,064 --> 00:36:51,733
-Right?
-An assault is

459
00:36:53,151 --> 00:36:55,153
supposed to be done with this.

460
00:36:55,236 --> 00:36:58,072
It means to hit with a fist.

461
00:36:58,156 --> 00:36:59,532
Doesn't it mean to hit and beat?

462
00:36:59,616 --> 00:37:00,867
No.

463
00:37:01,326 --> 00:37:04,203
It can be called an assault
only when someone is beaten by a fist.

464
00:37:04,537 --> 00:37:06,247
And?

465
00:37:06,539 --> 00:37:12,170
It sounded like Captain Ri hit him
with his hand open.

466
00:37:12,879 --> 00:37:15,256
That's what I heard, I believe.

467
00:37:16,382 --> 00:37:19,510
-Then it wasn't an assault.
-No, it wasn't.

468
00:37:21,596 --> 00:37:24,557
Where's Ri Jeong Hyeok, the poor man
who is behind bars for no reason?

469
00:37:24,641 --> 00:37:26,017
I shall bring him with me.

470
00:37:26,517 --> 00:37:29,520
RUN AWAY AND YOU DIE!
LET'S BUILD A STRONG SOCIALIST COUNTRY

471
00:37:31,731 --> 00:37:34,317
I'm sure you have learned
some lessons from this.

472
00:37:34,901 --> 00:37:35,860
First,

473
00:37:36,694 --> 00:37:39,405
all kinds of things can happen in life.

474
00:37:41,532 --> 00:37:44,243
Second, whenever that happens,

475
00:37:47,622 --> 00:37:48,915
come to me.

476
00:37:49,999 --> 00:37:52,710
You should have called me first.

477
00:37:53,670 --> 00:37:55,171
You should correct your mistake, okay?

478
00:37:56,464 --> 00:37:57,715
Okay.

479
00:37:58,549 --> 00:38:02,220
All right. You've been through a lot.
So take a good rest for the next days.

480
00:38:02,303 --> 00:38:05,890
My wife said she prepared a feast.

481
00:38:05,973 --> 00:38:07,433
So come to my place.

482
00:38:08,101 --> 00:38:09,435
I'd like to ask you for a favor.

483
00:38:10,019 --> 00:38:10,895
Okay.

484
00:38:11,646 --> 00:38:12,522
What is it?

485
00:38:13,815 --> 00:38:15,108
Tell me.

486
00:38:17,193 --> 00:38:20,279
I'll put the white radish salad here
because it's his favorite.

487
00:38:20,363 --> 00:38:21,447
Come on.

488
00:38:21,531 --> 00:38:23,074
Put it here.

489
00:38:23,157 --> 00:38:25,118
-Senior Colonel, you're back.
-Hi.

490
00:38:25,410 --> 00:38:27,870
Oh, my. Welcome.

491
00:38:32,250 --> 00:38:35,044
Why are you alone? Where is Jeong Hyeok?

492
00:38:36,003 --> 00:38:38,548
I don't know.
He said he had to hurry somewhere.

493
00:38:40,299 --> 00:38:43,010
By the way, he asked me for a weird favor.

494
00:38:44,262 --> 00:38:45,179
What favor?

495
00:39:03,740 --> 00:39:07,243
Jeong Hyeok must have gotten
his cooking skills from you.

496
00:39:07,326 --> 00:39:08,703
Did Jeong Hyeok

497
00:39:09,537 --> 00:39:10,872
make noodles for you?

498
00:39:10,955 --> 00:39:13,750
Yes, he made me great noodles

499
00:39:13,833 --> 00:39:15,501
and nice coffee too.

500
00:39:20,006 --> 00:39:23,342
He must have gotten
the kind heart from you.

501
00:39:27,472 --> 00:39:31,017
Jeong Hyeok, what do you think?
If you think it's too rushed...

502
00:39:32,310 --> 00:39:33,603
It's an old promise.

503
00:39:34,145 --> 00:39:35,104
I must keep it.

504
00:39:38,775 --> 00:39:41,527
Jeong Hyeok used to be a sweet boy,

505
00:39:42,779 --> 00:39:44,655
but he changed at some point.

506
00:39:46,532 --> 00:39:49,535
He has become cold
and wouldn't let anyone be with him.

507
00:39:51,412 --> 00:39:52,789
But you just said he's kind.

508
00:39:54,832 --> 00:39:55,958
I'm glad to hear that.

509
00:40:22,443 --> 00:40:23,736
Where is she?

510
00:40:23,820 --> 00:40:24,904
Who?

511
00:40:24,987 --> 00:40:26,405
You know who I'm talking about.

512
00:40:26,489 --> 00:40:29,116
I know you took that woman.

513
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:32,078
-Where is she?
-Where should I hide?

514
00:40:32,870 --> 00:40:35,289
Don't worry and just tell him
you don't know anything.

515
00:40:36,040 --> 00:40:37,708
I have...

