784
01:01:29,053 --> 01:01:30,221
Yes, sir.

785
01:01:30,304 --> 01:01:33,182
We briefly met at Ri Jeong Hyeok's ward.

786
01:01:34,183 --> 01:01:35,434
Right, we did.

787
01:01:35,518 --> 01:01:38,104
How did the two of you come together?

788
01:01:38,938 --> 01:01:40,022
He tipped me off

789
01:01:40,982 --> 01:01:44,569
about something strange.

790
01:01:46,785 --> 01:01:47,969
"Tipped off"?

791
01:01:49,323 --> 01:01:51,993
He said a person wanted
by the State Security Department

792
01:01:52,076 --> 01:01:53,744
is hiding here.

793
01:01:53,828 --> 01:01:57,248
I'm not sure
whether I should believe him or not.

794
01:01:57,915 --> 01:01:58,958
Are you saying

795
01:01:59,041 --> 01:02:02,211
you want to search my house or something?

796
01:02:02,295 --> 01:02:04,005
No way.

797
01:02:04,088 --> 01:02:05,506
I wouldn't dare.

798
01:02:05,590 --> 01:02:08,593
But if such a person is hiding here,

799
01:02:08,676 --> 01:02:11,262
that person might harm you.

800
01:02:11,387 --> 01:02:13,514
That would be terrible.

801
01:02:14,849 --> 01:02:17,685
Thanks for worrying about me.

802
01:02:21,284 --> 01:02:22,703
URGENT INVESTIGATION REQUEST

803
01:02:23,578 --> 01:02:26,873
This is an urgent investigation request
from the State Security Department.

804
01:02:26,957 --> 01:02:30,544
I'm afraid we will have to search
your house for a moment, sir.

805
01:02:31,128 --> 01:02:32,963
This is just for the sake of formality.

806
01:02:33,046 --> 01:02:35,007
Carry it out with utmost respect.

807
01:02:35,799 --> 01:02:37,342
-Search.
-Yes, sir!

808
01:02:57,750 --> 01:02:59,418
Unbelievable.

809
01:02:59,960 --> 01:03:01,962
An emergency switch?

810
01:03:02,045 --> 01:03:03,714
An emergency switch, for goodness' sake.

811
01:03:04,339 --> 01:03:07,176
I thought that the fact
Captain Ri is the son of

812
01:03:07,259 --> 01:03:10,387
Director of the General Political Bureau
might somehow benefit us too,

813
01:03:10,471 --> 01:03:12,264
as we're his subordinates.

814
01:03:12,347 --> 01:03:14,183
Benefit, my foot. This is just shocking.

815
01:03:14,592 --> 01:03:15,768
We were

816
01:03:16,018 --> 01:03:18,020
supposed to be on duty next spring.

817
01:03:18,103 --> 01:03:19,062
Hey.

818
01:03:19,791 --> 01:03:23,192
We all got fooled by Captain Ri's lies.

819
01:03:24,568 --> 01:03:26,069
Think about it.

820
01:03:26,695 --> 01:03:29,823
If he was actually the son of the Director
of the General Political Bureau,

821
01:03:30,199 --> 01:03:33,327
why would he get shot on the street
and put behind bars?

822
01:03:34,077 --> 01:03:36,872
He probably told us lies
based on his personal hope

823
01:03:36,955 --> 01:03:41,251
that in his afterlife,
he would like to be born as a son

824
01:03:41,335 --> 01:03:44,713
of the Director
of the General Political Bureau,

825
01:03:44,797 --> 01:03:47,007
and we all got fooled by it.

826
01:03:47,174 --> 01:03:49,968
Why aren't you saying anything?

827
01:03:53,514 --> 01:03:56,934
Is there something
you heard from Captain Ri?

828
01:03:59,144 --> 01:04:03,232
<i>So what favor
did Jeong Hyeok ask of the Senior Colonel?</i>

829
01:04:03,816 --> 01:04:06,610
Jeong Hyeok said to my husband...

830
01:04:07,361 --> 01:04:08,987
I would like to ask you for a favor.

831
01:04:10,172 --> 01:04:11,198
Okay.

832
01:04:11,949 --> 01:04:12,825
What is it?

833
01:04:14,117 --> 01:04:15,202
Tell me.

834
01:04:16,245 --> 01:04:19,331
I would like you to include my company
in the emergency switch.

835
01:04:21,166 --> 01:04:22,543
But it's cold winter now.

836
01:04:22,668 --> 01:04:25,462
He asked him to deploy them
at the frontline?

837
01:04:25,546 --> 01:04:26,839
Frontline?

838
01:04:26,922 --> 01:04:30,634
Has he lost his mind
after his time in the detention center?

839
01:04:31,051 --> 01:04:32,673
Why would he ask that?

840
01:04:44,788 --> 01:04:48,068
<i>Captain Ri will go
to the frontline with Se-ri.</i>

841
01:04:48,277 --> 01:04:50,404
<i>That's why he asked
for the emergency switch.</i>

842
01:04:50,487 --> 01:04:53,156
What? What do you mean?
Why do they go there?

843
01:04:53,240 --> 01:04:55,325
She's going back to where she came from.

844
01:04:55,409 --> 01:04:57,160
But that doesn't make any...

845
01:04:57,244 --> 01:04:59,872
If he can bring her back in there somehow,

846
01:05:00,372 --> 01:05:02,541
it isn't complete nonsense.

847
01:05:03,125 --> 01:05:04,668
I guess you're right.

848
01:05:05,127 --> 01:05:08,422
No others know that area better than us.

849
01:05:09,006 --> 01:05:10,716
I mean, we guard the guard post too.

850
01:05:10,799 --> 01:05:13,051
We search the area,

851
01:05:13,135 --> 01:05:15,721
and Captain Ri is the officer in charge.

852
01:05:15,804 --> 01:05:17,014
That area

853
01:05:17,097 --> 01:05:18,932
is our area.

854
01:05:32,854 --> 01:05:35,324
BORDER

855
01:05:36,060 --> 01:05:41,204
DMZ NORTH ENTRANCE 1

856
01:06:12,778 --> 01:06:15,280
I am glad that you are looking out for me,

857
01:06:15,364 --> 01:06:17,366
but this should be enough.

858
01:06:17,783 --> 01:06:19,284
The sun will set soon.

859
01:06:19,868 --> 01:06:20,869
Of course.

860
01:06:21,370 --> 01:06:24,623
It seems like I was given a false report.

861
01:06:27,852 --> 01:06:29,086
You punk.

862
01:06:29,169 --> 01:06:31,129
You scum!

863
01:06:31,463 --> 01:06:34,424
Do you know where we are right now?
What are you playing at?

864
01:06:34,508 --> 01:06:36,635
That's enough.

865
01:06:37,344 --> 01:06:39,513
Didn't Jeong Hyeok visit you?

866
01:06:39,596 --> 01:06:41,640
Didn't he hide that woman?

867
01:06:41,723 --> 01:06:42,891
Hey!

868
01:06:45,519 --> 01:06:47,145
It seems like you haven't heard the news.

869
01:06:47,729 --> 01:06:49,523
There has been an emergency company switch

870
01:06:49,606 --> 01:06:51,525
due to a deserter at the frontline.

871
01:06:51,608 --> 01:06:56,113
My son should be at the frontline
right now as the captain of the company.

872
01:06:56,560 --> 01:06:57,823
I had no idea.

873
01:06:58,407 --> 01:07:01,326
-I apologize for our discourtesy, sir.
-That's the place.

874
01:07:01,410 --> 01:07:03,453
He went to the frontline

875
01:07:04,329 --> 01:07:07,457
-to send that woman to the south.
-Shut your mouth.

876
01:07:07,541 --> 01:07:08,750
I know I am right.

877
01:07:08,834 --> 01:07:12,087
There is a chance they entered
the demilitarized zone.

878
01:07:14,089 --> 01:07:15,549
I apologize, sir.

879
01:07:15,632 --> 01:07:17,801
I will take care of him.

880
01:07:18,658 --> 01:07:20,012
Drag him away.

881
01:07:21,555 --> 01:07:22,639
Sir.

882
01:08:04,695 --> 01:08:07,990
I didn't know there would be a village
in the demilitarized zone.

883
01:08:09,199 --> 01:08:11,284
People lived here before the war.

884
01:08:11,868 --> 01:08:15,914
This house is in the best shape.

885
01:08:16,899 --> 01:08:18,625
Come and sit down.

886
01:08:27,175 --> 01:08:28,343
All right.

887
01:08:29,761 --> 01:08:33,306
This isn't alcohol, but medicine.

888
01:08:34,516 --> 01:08:40,772
It must have been made before 1953--

889
01:08:40,856 --> 01:08:42,190
Master Sergeant Pyo.

890
01:08:43,275 --> 01:08:44,526
Yes, sir.

891
01:08:50,782 --> 01:08:54,202
Why is there a bowl on top of that crock?

892
01:08:55,412 --> 01:08:57,379
It's a bowl for fresh water.

893
01:08:58,165 --> 01:09:00,208
You mean the kind
that was used for prayer?

894
01:09:00,292 --> 01:09:01,626
Yes.

895
01:09:03,086 --> 01:09:06,506
I think the person who lived here
had a son who went off to war.

896
01:09:09,176 --> 01:09:11,303
There are his photos in the room.

897
01:09:12,345 --> 01:09:16,016
We never touch one of those bowls.

898
01:09:16,975 --> 01:09:18,143
All of us have

899
01:09:19,561 --> 01:09:21,021
a mother.

900
01:09:26,109 --> 01:09:29,696
Your mother will be happy
once you go back.

901
01:09:29,780 --> 01:09:31,239
She must have waited for you.

902
01:09:35,494 --> 01:09:36,578
I don't know.

903
01:09:39,915 --> 01:09:41,124
Oh, you can see it from here.

904
01:09:42,292 --> 01:09:43,502
See what?

905
01:09:44,795 --> 01:09:47,047
Do you see that tiny mountain?

906
01:09:48,006 --> 01:09:49,716
-Yes.
-It's Mount Bukhan.

907
01:09:49,800 --> 01:09:50,967
It's in Seoul, right?

908
01:09:51,676 --> 01:09:52,594
Really?

909
01:09:53,386 --> 01:09:55,138
Is it so close?

910
01:09:55,764 --> 01:09:57,641
Even though it's so close,

911
01:09:58,767 --> 01:09:59,726
we won't

912
01:10:00,560 --> 01:10:02,049
see each other again, right?

913
01:10:05,677 --> 01:10:06,650
Still,

914
01:10:07,192 --> 01:10:09,550
you will see your mother.

915
01:10:09,903 --> 01:10:11,279
I am jealous.

916
01:10:13,240 --> 01:10:16,535
I am not that close with my mom.

917
01:10:18,620 --> 01:10:21,790
You will be able to see your mom
after being discharged.

918
01:10:23,041 --> 01:10:24,334
Are you making fun of him?

919
01:10:24,417 --> 01:10:27,254
He has nine years and seven months to go
before discharge.

920
01:10:27,337 --> 01:10:28,380
What?

921
01:10:28,964 --> 01:10:30,215
Nine years and seven months?

922
01:10:31,627 --> 01:10:33,635
That's a long time.

923
01:10:35,053 --> 01:10:36,221
Eun Dong,

924
01:10:36,304 --> 01:10:38,056
you must miss your mom a lot.

925
01:10:39,099 --> 01:10:40,016
Yes.

926
01:10:41,768 --> 01:10:44,437
I miss her. I am worried about her.

927
01:10:46,106 --> 01:10:48,441
My hometown is colder than it is here.

928
01:10:49,067 --> 01:10:50,819
I wonder if there is enough firewood.

929
01:10:51,361 --> 01:10:53,363
I wonder if my siblings are eating well.

930
01:10:54,114 --> 01:10:55,448
My youngest sibling

931
01:10:56,199 --> 01:10:57,450
is weak,

932
01:10:58,577 --> 01:11:00,078
so he gets sick often.

933
01:11:03,081 --> 01:11:04,541
I am sure all of them are doing well.

934
01:11:06,501 --> 01:11:09,838
Everyone, don't get hurt.

935
01:11:09,921 --> 01:11:12,591
Make sure you eat well.

936
01:11:12,966 --> 01:11:14,247
Stay healthy

937
01:11:17,387 --> 01:11:18,930
and live well, okay?

938
01:11:21,683 --> 01:11:22,991
You never know.

939
01:11:23,810 --> 01:11:25,896
The two countries might suddenly reunify.

940
01:11:27,439 --> 01:11:30,734
Stop talking nonsense.
Live well when you go home.

941
01:11:31,359 --> 01:11:33,486
If you come back again, I will...

942
01:11:35,071 --> 01:11:35,989
I will bury you

943
01:11:37,991 --> 01:11:38,825
at a mountain

944
01:11:39,492 --> 01:11:40,577
or a river.

945
01:11:43,288 --> 01:11:44,372
Suit yourself.

946
01:11:46,166 --> 01:11:48,376
Bury me at a mountain or a river.

947
01:11:51,963 --> 01:11:52,881
The sun

948
01:11:53,548 --> 01:11:55,550
should set already.

949
01:11:57,177 --> 01:12:00,680
That noisy woman can leave
only when it's dark.

950
01:12:14,715 --> 01:12:18,073
Mother, we need to call a locksmith.
There is no master key either.

951
01:12:24,746 --> 01:12:27,165
What brings you here?

952
01:12:27,249 --> 01:12:28,750
Open the door.

953
01:12:37,926 --> 01:12:39,177
The passcode is my birthday.

954
01:12:41,680 --> 01:12:42,889
The day I almost died.

955
01:12:52,941 --> 01:12:54,609
Mother, how did you know the passcode?

956
01:12:55,360 --> 01:12:57,862
She is incredible.
How does she know everything?

957
01:12:57,946 --> 01:12:59,489
Maybe she can enter my house too.

958
01:12:59,990 --> 01:13:01,157
Aren't you worried?

959
01:13:08,873 --> 01:13:10,500
My goodness.

960
01:13:11,001 --> 01:13:14,462
I wonder who had taken it
from the auction in Hong Kong.

961
01:13:14,546 --> 01:13:16,214
It was here.

962
01:13:33,815 --> 01:13:34,941
I prepared coffee.

963
01:13:37,110 --> 01:13:38,194
Thank you.

964
01:13:44,993 --> 01:13:46,077
By the way,

965
01:13:47,078 --> 01:13:48,413
what brings you here?

966
01:13:50,832 --> 01:13:52,042
So you will list your company.

967
01:13:53,918 --> 01:13:57,213
You must know that
your brothers aren't doing so well.

968
01:13:58,757 --> 01:13:59,674
Must you

969
01:14:00,216 --> 01:14:01,176
do that?

970
01:14:02,844 --> 01:14:06,181
My brothers and my dad have nothing to do
with my company.

971
01:14:06,431 --> 01:14:09,392
I founded it and raised it.
Now, I will list it.

972
01:14:09,476 --> 01:14:10,560
Mom.

973
01:14:11,770 --> 01:14:16,024
It wasn't easy to get this far by myself.
It was really hard.

974
01:14:18,568 --> 01:14:20,068
No one asked you to do that.

975
01:14:24,324 --> 01:14:26,926
I know exactly what you are playing at.

976
01:14:27,702 --> 01:14:29,496
You want your father to see it

977
01:14:30,080 --> 01:14:32,749
and realize that
you are better than your brothers.

978
01:14:32,832 --> 01:14:35,585
You want to get chosen.
You want to take everything!

979
01:14:37,003 --> 01:14:38,880
-Mom.
-"Mom"?

980
01:14:40,090 --> 01:14:41,883
If you let go of your greed,

981
01:14:42,300 --> 01:14:44,844
we can have an easy relationship

982
01:14:44,928 --> 01:14:46,596
like a real mother and a daughter.

983
01:14:46,679 --> 01:14:47,931
It isn't greed.

984
01:14:49,307 --> 01:14:50,392
It's my dream.

985
01:14:51,518 --> 01:14:52,435
Do you think

986
01:14:52,894 --> 01:14:54,270
you deserve that luxury?

987
01:14:56,064 --> 01:14:57,190
Because of you,

988
01:14:58,691 --> 01:15:00,318
my life is hell.

989
01:15:09,347 --> 01:15:10,495
My goodness.

990
01:15:12,372 --> 01:15:14,666
Mother, do you see this engraving?

991
01:15:15,375 --> 01:15:18,837
Designer Jean Merritt passed away
right after she signed an autograph.

992
01:15:19,504 --> 01:15:22,757
This is the bag, Mother. My goodness.

993
01:15:22,841 --> 01:15:23,967
Put it down.

994
01:15:25,051 --> 01:15:26,344
-Okay.
-Come on out.

995
01:15:26,428 --> 01:15:28,721
-Right now?
-Yes.

996
01:15:36,354 --> 01:15:37,564
What are you doing?

997
01:15:39,774 --> 01:15:43,736
We need to merge or take over
Se-ri's Choice eventually.

998
01:15:43,820 --> 01:15:45,238
These documents might help.

999
01:15:47,594 --> 01:15:50,326
EXCELLENT COMPANY AWARD
WOMAN CEO OF THE YEAR

1000
01:16:02,005 --> 01:16:04,466
Mother, isn't it you?

1001
01:16:05,049 --> 01:16:06,134
I think it is.

1002
01:16:37,707 --> 01:16:38,833
Take care.

1003
01:16:41,002 --> 01:16:43,880
Go back to your life
as if nothing had happened.

1004
01:16:46,216 --> 01:16:48,384
You are in no position to worry about me.

1005
01:16:48,801 --> 01:16:51,638
Don't worry about me. I will be okay.

1006
01:16:52,180 --> 01:16:56,142
I have so much work waiting for me.
I will get used to my old life in no time.

1007
01:16:56,643 --> 01:17:01,189
As always,
I will earn and spend money well,

1008
01:17:01,773 --> 01:17:05,068
work diligently, and date men.

1009
01:17:08,530 --> 01:17:10,323
"Date men"?

1010
01:17:12,367 --> 01:17:14,327
Should I not do that?

1011
01:17:15,537 --> 01:17:16,829
Well,

1012
01:17:18,039 --> 01:17:19,123
it's up to you.

1013
01:17:20,500 --> 01:17:22,085
Didn't you say we should have

1014
01:17:22,710 --> 01:17:24,462
a post-breakup condolence period?

1015
01:17:27,173 --> 01:17:29,074
I believe it was six months.

1016
01:17:31,606 --> 01:17:34,223
I simply meant you should do it.

1017
01:17:34,973 --> 01:17:37,809
You told me to go back to my life.

1018
01:17:38,308 --> 01:17:40,436
I didn't tell you to go back to men.

1019
01:17:41,312 --> 01:17:44,357
You told me to do so
as if nothing had happened.

1020
01:17:45,316 --> 01:17:47,485
I didn't tell you to cozy up to men.

1021
01:17:51,698 --> 01:17:53,241
Is a period of six months

1022
01:17:53,741 --> 01:17:54,576
enough?

1023
01:17:58,162 --> 01:17:59,414
Sure.

1024
01:18:02,000 --> 01:18:03,042
Okay.

1025
01:18:03,876 --> 01:18:05,295
For six months,

1026
01:18:06,963 --> 01:18:08,840
I will have a condolence period.

1027
01:18:12,135 --> 01:18:13,511
It was fate.

1028
01:18:14,721 --> 01:18:15,847
Think about it.

1029
01:18:16,252 --> 01:18:19,225
It's incredible
that we met by chance in Switzerland

1030
01:18:20,018 --> 01:18:22,729
and then in North Korea.

1031
01:18:26,399 --> 01:18:27,275
What is it?

1032
01:18:34,532 --> 01:18:36,075
You can date men

1033
01:18:37,994 --> 01:18:41,414
and hang out with other people
as if nothing had happened.

1034
01:18:44,000 --> 01:18:45,209
But

1035
01:18:47,003 --> 01:18:48,338
don't be lonely again.

1036
01:18:50,465 --> 01:18:54,886
Don't ever think about disappearing
at a scenic place.

1037
01:18:58,473 --> 01:18:59,599
You have me.

1038
01:19:00,933 --> 01:19:02,602
You won't be by my side.

1039
01:19:04,937 --> 01:19:06,272
I won't be by your side,

1040
01:19:08,316 --> 01:19:10,485
but I will always hope

1041
01:19:12,362 --> 01:19:13,529
that you won't be lonely.

1042
01:19:18,534 --> 01:19:19,619
Be happy

1043
01:19:20,703 --> 01:19:21,788
until the end of your life.

1044
01:19:25,083 --> 01:19:26,501
I would be grateful if you do that.

1045
01:19:32,340 --> 01:19:33,549
How do you

1046
01:19:34,092 --> 01:19:35,885
reach the border from here?

1047
01:19:38,221 --> 01:19:42,058
If you go that way,
you reach Yeokgok Stream.

1048
01:19:46,896 --> 01:19:48,861
<i>There is a small boat.</i>

1049
01:19:50,024 --> 01:19:54,737
<i>People hid it to catch fish with grenades
when the water level rises.</i>

1050
01:20:24,976 --> 01:20:26,436
<i>Then comes a mine-free path.</i>

1051
01:20:27,270 --> 01:20:29,272
<i>It's marked</i>

1052
01:20:29,522 --> 01:20:32,442
<i>with square granite rocks
that are about 40cm tall.</i>

1053
01:20:34,402 --> 01:20:38,990
<i>There are no mines within the 10m radius.</i>

1054
01:20:42,493 --> 01:20:47,165
<i>If you walk down that path,
you will reach the Southern Limit Line.</i>

1055
01:20:48,875 --> 01:20:51,878
-It's not far from here.
-That's right.

1056
01:20:52,462 --> 01:20:55,616
A round trip should take
about an hour or two...

1057
01:21:01,053 --> 01:21:02,972
The hour is...

1058
01:21:03,765 --> 01:21:05,266
Dawn will break soon.

1059
01:21:05,349 --> 01:21:06,809
Why isn't he back yet?

1060
01:21:07,560 --> 01:21:09,061
Maybe he got lost.

1061
01:21:09,687 --> 01:21:11,230
No way.

1062
01:21:21,407 --> 01:21:22,700
What is it?

1063
01:21:25,161 --> 01:21:26,579
This is a wrong path.

1064
01:21:27,455 --> 01:21:28,456
Again?

1065
01:21:30,041 --> 01:21:31,292
We keep finding the wrong path.

1066
01:21:36,464 --> 01:21:38,257
I think I saw that place before.

1067
01:21:43,012 --> 01:21:45,765
The paths look alike, so...

1068
01:21:45,848 --> 01:21:47,058
Ri Jeong Hyeok.

1069
01:21:48,184 --> 01:21:49,412
Be honest with me.

1070
01:21:50,436 --> 01:21:52,688
-What?
-You have no sense of direction, right?

1071
01:21:53,356 --> 01:21:57,151
<i>Among us, Captain Ri is the best
at finding the right direction</i>

1072
01:21:57,235 --> 01:21:58,986
<i>even in the dark.</i>

1073
01:21:59,070 --> 01:21:59,904
Yes.

1074
01:22:01,447 --> 01:22:04,075
I am bad at finding the right direction

1075
01:22:06,160 --> 01:22:07,578
in the dark.

1076
01:22:10,164 --> 01:22:11,207
I am sorry.

1077
01:22:14,210 --> 01:22:18,840
The fact he hasn't come back yet means

1078
01:22:19,924 --> 01:22:22,593
he has either gotten into an accident...

1079
01:22:22,677 --> 01:22:23,845
-What?
-What?

1080
01:22:24,720 --> 01:22:26,264
Or he wants to spend more time

1081
01:22:27,014 --> 01:22:28,391
with her.

1082
01:22:29,308 --> 01:22:30,726
-Right.
-I see.

1083
01:22:53,124 --> 01:22:54,208
We are here.

1084
01:22:59,755 --> 01:23:02,216
We are finally here.

1085
01:23:05,428 --> 01:23:07,054
Do you see that tree over there?

1086
01:23:12,602 --> 01:23:14,562
Walk toward that tree.

1087
01:23:14,937 --> 01:23:18,232
That's the entrance
of the South Korean search team.

1088
01:23:20,693 --> 01:23:23,112
The search team will do a round
in the morning,

1089
01:23:23,195 --> 01:23:24,530
so ask them for help.

1090
01:23:27,783 --> 01:23:28,784
By any chance,

1091
01:23:30,786 --> 01:23:33,706
can you walk me there?

1092
01:23:37,251 --> 01:23:38,836
I can't take a single step

1093
01:23:39,378 --> 01:23:40,588
over this line.

1094
01:23:48,930 --> 01:23:52,016
Don't forget to keep your eyes
on the rocks.

1095
01:23:59,607 --> 01:24:00,775
Jeong Hyeok,

1096
01:24:01,859 --> 01:24:03,235
don't forget about me.

1097
01:24:05,154 --> 01:24:05,988
I won't.

1098
01:24:06,072 --> 01:24:10,117
How would I forget about a woman
who fell from the sky?

1099
01:24:11,911 --> 01:24:13,496
I didn't fall.

1100
01:24:13,579 --> 01:24:14,538
I descended.

1101
01:24:16,666 --> 01:24:17,875
Sure.

1102
01:24:26,425 --> 01:24:27,301
I will get going now.

1103
01:25:24,358 --> 01:25:25,568
A single step

1104
01:25:28,070 --> 01:25:29,113
should be okay.

1105
01:26:40,142 --> 01:26:42,436
I can't believe him.

1106
01:26:43,187 --> 01:26:47,691
All the books are dark and difficult.

1107
01:27:38,742 --> 01:27:41,287
I LOVE YOU

1108
01:27:43,789 --> 01:27:46,667
RI JEONG HYEOK

1109
01:27:49,295 --> 01:27:54,175
I LOVE YOU RI JEONG HYEOK

1110
